How can I write a Java program that outputs the third person singular in the imperative form of the verb 'play' and its other forms, including the infinitive form, present participle, and past participle of the verb?
Here is a sample Java code to achieve this:
import java.util.*;
public class VerbForms {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      Map<String, String[]> verbForms = new HashMap<String, String[]>();
      verbForms.put("play", new String[]{"play", "playing", "played", "plays"});
      String[] forms = verbForms.get("play");
      System.out.println("Imperative (Third Person Singular): " + forms[3]);
      System.out.println("Infinitive: " + forms[0]);
      System.out.println("Present Participle: " + forms[1]);
      System.out.println("Past Participle: " + forms[2]);
   }
}
Hope this helps!
